The paper focuses on the alignment of geometric patterns, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves compressing high dimensional data, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of the doubling dimension to measure compression and approximation is a concept from computational geometry (cs.CG) and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely to be relevant to this paper.
